Equine rhinopneumonitis, Chile
------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 3 Dec 2013 from Dr Victor Ramirez Arias, Head, Division of Animal Protection, Livestock and Agriculture Service (SAG), Ministry of Agriculture, Santiago, Chile

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 1 Oct 2013
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 9 Oct 2013
Report date: 3 Dec 2013
Date submitted to OIE: 3 Dec 2013
Reason for notification: new strain of a listed disease
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Equid herpesvirus 4 [EHV-4]
Nature of diagnosis: suspicion, clinical, laboratory (basic), laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks:
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1 (Foco 1 Haras Sumaya): Pirque, Cordillera, Santiago Metropolitan Region
Date of start of the outbreak: 1 Oct 2013
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: not applicable
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Equidae / 55 / 1 / 0 / 0 / 0 /
Affected population: thoroughbred horse with respiratory signs and vaccinated against rhinopneumonitis.
Outbreak statistics:
Species / Apparent morbidity rate / Apparent mortality rate / Apparent case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Equidae / 1.82 percent / 0 percent / 0 percent / 0 percent
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: the presence of equid herpesvirus 4 (EHV-4) was suspected since some time ago, but for the 1st time it has been confirmed by PCR.

Control measures
Measures applied: no vaccination, treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Official Laboratory Lo Aguirre (national laboratory) / Equine / nested RT-PCR / 9 Oct 2013 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

